@smstxtmsg @eigenrobot @QiaochuYuan The word for conscience (συνείδησις) is found ~30 times in the N.T.

The key passages are Rom. 2:15, 1 Cor. 8 (cf. Romans 14), and 1 Cor. 10:23-33.

Essentially, it refers to your consciousness (awareness or sense) of what you believe is right and wrong.

